completion:
for the number of homicides in a year.  I am sure that the Baltimore Police Department is doing everything they can to stop the killings.  But they are not getting enough help from the mayor and the governor.  The result is that Baltimore is now the most dangerous city in America.  And the mayor of Baltimore is not happy that President Trump is pointing this out.  The following comes from  The Baltimore Sun …
Baltimore Mayor Catherine Pugh said Wednesday that President Donald Trump is using the city’s high homicide rate as a political tool to divide the country and that his tweets about the city are “unacceptable.”
The president has repeatedly criticized the city’s crime rate and the mayor’s handling of it, tweeting on Wednesday that the city is “a mess.”
The city has set a record for homicides this year, with 342 people killed in the city as of Tuesday. The previous record was 338 in 1993.
So why is Baltimore so dangerous?  The following comes from  a recent article  by James Robbins…
The city’s homicide rate is more than six times the national average, and its violent crime rate is nearly 10 times the national average. Baltimore has more murders than Chicago, New York, and Los Angeles combined.  Baltimore’s murder rate is 56 per 100,000 residents. By comparison, Chicago’s is 15 per 100,000 residents, and New York City’s is 3 per 100,000 residents.
So what is the mayor of Baltimore doing about this crisis?
Well, she is spending her time trying to get the president to stop talking about Baltimore.  The following comes from  a recent article  by John Hayward…
Baltimore Mayor Catherine Pugh complained that President Trump is using her city as a political punching bag, and demanded he stop talking about the city’s murder epidemic. She is the mayor of a city with more murders than Chicago, New York, and Los Angeles combined, and she thinks the president should shut up about it.
Pugh told reporters, “I think it’s unacceptable for the president to use Baltimore as a political tool to divide this country. We are a city that has been working hard to come together and to do the things that we need to do to make sure that we are safe, that we are healthy, that we have a great quality of life. And to have the president use us as a political tool to divide this country is unacceptable.”
Baltimore is a mess. No Human Life is valued.
